They reduce flakiness and increase maintainability of UI tests.”


Now Playwright (LIGHT KNOWLEDGE)

Salesforce LOVES Playwright syntax because it uses semantic locators.

You only need these:

🟩 2. PLAYWRIGHT LOCATORS (LIGHT)
⭐ A. getByRole()

MOST RECOMMENDED — stable & semantic.

page.get_by_role("button", name="Login")
page.get_by_role("textbox", name="Email")


Why?

Uses ARIA roles- ARIA give semantic meaning to elements, allows screen readers to present and support interaction with object

Less flaky

Very readable

⭐ B. getByText()
page.get_by_text("Submit")


Useful when role isn’t available.

⭐ C. getByPlaceholder()
page.get_by_placeholder("Enter email")


Very clean for input fields.

⭐ D. getByTestId() (BEST)
page.get_by_test_id("login-btn")


Similar to Cypress data-testid.

⭐ E. locator()
page.locator("#username")
page.locator(".btn-primary")


Equivalent to Cypress cy.get().

🟥 What to AVOID in Playwright

❌ Long chained XPath
❌ Text locators for dynamic text
❌ Selectors tied to styling

